@NODE "Installing" "Installing"




                    To Install this Internet Package.
                   ************************************


1. You now only need to have the archive's that you have not
   already got installed on you system to use this package.

   Make sure all the other files needed are in the same directory
   as each other.

   Miami   Any version but must be the Lha version except 2.1.
   GRn_2.1a.lha
   NewsAgent14.lha
   Geditor.lha
   DaFTP   Any version but must be the Lha version.
   YAM13_4.lha
   WBRun_fix.lha
   CDRun.lha
   Extras2-5.lha
   IBrowse   Any version but must be the Lha version.
   AmTelnet  Any version but must be the Lha version.

   There are link's to these files on my website.
   ( http://www.cliffe.demon.co.uk)
   

2. Run the Install script.

   Select the location on your system where you want to install this package   
   A drawer called NetFace will be created there.
   
   Enter the information asked for.
   
   This will take about 5 minutes to install.



3. Open the drawer that has just been created.

   Run the program called Miami Init that is in the Miami drawer.

   Enter the details as asked for,

   Phone no    = 

   IP Address  = Dynamic

   Protocal    = PPP or SLIP
   
   Login Name

   Login Password
   
   When entered proceed

   In the new window click on dial

   When login prompt click on send login

   When password prompt click on send password

   After 2-3 minutes when you may be asked if you want to add a DNS server 
   select yes and enter your providers number if you know it in the string 
   gadget.

   When asked for another select no unless you have more than one number.
   
   The modem will than dis-connect.

   Untick the PRT box unless you have a printer switched on and ready.

   Enter your RealName in the new window.

   Exit program.

   Run Miami

   Select Import from MiamiInit from the settings menu.
   
   And select MiamiInit.config from the requester.
   
   From the settings menu select save as default.
   
   Exit program and close Miami Drawer
   


4. Run the program NetFace and click on the button called Mail.


   From the settings menu select Configuration,

   On the start page enter the required info,
   
   Real name           Your real name.
   
   Email Address       Your email address.
   
   Pop 3 server        Service providers pop3 address.
   
   Password            Your login password.
   
   
   
   On the Receive page enter the required info
   
   POP3 User ID           Your username.
   
   Select get mail on startup
   
   
   On the Send Page enter the required info
   
   SMTP Server        Your service providers mail address.

   Reply to           Your Email address.
   
   Organization       Private
   
   Select send mail on startup
   
   
   Write Page
   
   select use signature


   On the System Page enter the required info

   External Editor    NetFace:Geditor/Geditor


   Select save

   Quit Program


   REBOOT.





